{
  "question_id": "10865336-765b-45f1-b6ea-dea2a2ebb41b",
  "short_text": "Split Numbers",
  "content": "Given space-separated numbers, write a program to print a list containing the given numbers\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing space-separated integers.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be a single line containing a list of given integers.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given space-separated numbers are `10 20 30 40 50`,\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n[10, 20, 30, 40, 50]\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "2c6eb386-9759-4722-9472-dd005ad3b679",
      "code_content": "numbers = input()\n\nnumbers_list = numbers.split()\n\nresultant_list = []\n\nfor number in numbers_list:\n    number = int(number)\n\n    resultant_list += [number]\n\nprint(resultant_list)",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
